Canadian Stocks Rise as Oil Climbs, Research In Motion Gains

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-02-16T15:14:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/augusta-resource-rogers-talisman-energy-canada-equity-preview.html
Canadian stocks rose for a third
straight day as oil rebounded from an 11-week low and  Research
In Motion Ltd . gained.  RIM rose 2.7 percent, after Citigroup Inc. said the maker
of the BlackBerry smartphone will benefit from the “commotion”
caused by Nokia Oyj’s alliance with Microsoft Corp.  Bank of
Montreal  gained 0.6 percent, after it was raised to “neutral”
from “underperform” at Credit Suisse Group AG.  Canadian
Natural Resources Ltd ., the second-largest energy company by
market value, increased 1.8 percent as oil rebounded from an 11-
week low.  The Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index rose 33.9 points,
or 0.2 percent, to 13,963.2 at 9:50 a.m. in Toronto after
reaching 13,992.4, the highest intraday level since July 2008.  The S&P/TSX gained 3.6 percent from the beginning of the
year through yesterday as economic data and corporate earnings
signaled the global economic recovery is becoming more
entrenched. Gold rose 3 percent this month through yesterday.
The precious metal has advanced on concern over inflation in
emerging markets and  Europe  and the strife in the Middle East.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Johnson in New York at 
